  <summary>9/4/1997--Introduced.
Condemns the bombing in Jerusalem on September 4, 1997, and those responsible for encouraging or inciting it. Expresses: (1) condolences to the families of the victims; and (2) solidarity with the people of Israel. Reaffirms that the United States should fully cooperate with Israel in helping to stem the tide of terrorism which has threatened the Oslo process and the stability of the region. Affirms that the United States should not provide monetary or other assistance to the Palestinian Authority until it has fulfilled its obligations under the Oslo Accords.</summary>
